## Data Flow & Sources

### 1️⃣ User Data Input

| Data Type | Source | Collection Point | Storage |
|-----------|--------|------------------|---------|
| **Profile Data** | User onboarding form | `/onboarding` endpoint | MongoDB `users` collection |
| **Cycle Information** | Onboarding form | Cycle length, last period date | MongoDB `users.cycle_data` |
| **Health Goals** | Onboarding form | User-entered goals | MongoDB `users.cycle_data.health_goals` |
| **Daily Check-ins** | Check-in form | Mood, pain level, symptoms | MongoDB `messages` (as context) |
| **Chat Messages** | Chat interface | User questions/responses | MongoDB `messages` collection |
| **Voice Input** | Audio recording | `/voice-chat` endpoint | Transcribed to text, then stored |

### 2️⃣ Knowledge Base (RAG System)

```
data/health_kb.txt
├── Menstrual cycle phase information
├── Exercise recommendations per phase
├── Nutrition advice (iron-rich foods, etc.)
├── Common conditions (PCOS, Endometriosis)
├── PMS symptom management
└── Cycle tracking benefits
```

**How RAG Works:**
1. Knowledge base is chunked into sentences (min 20 chars)
2. Chunks are embedded using `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2`
3. Embeddings are indexed in FAISS for fast similarity search
4. User queries are embedded and matched against the index
5. Top 3 relevant chunks are retrieved and injected into AI context

### 3️⃣ External Data Sources

| Source | Purpose | Integration |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| **Google Gemini 2.5 Flash** | AI conversation, content generation | `google-generativeai` SDK |
| **ElevenLabs** | Premium text-to-speech | `elevenlabs` SDK (optional) |
| **gTTS** | Fallback text-to-speech | `gTTS` library (free) |
| **Algorand Testnet** | Consent recording | `py-algorand-sdk` |

