## Database Schema

### MongoDB Collections

#### `users` Collection
```javascript
{
    "user_id": "string",           // Unique identifier
    "cycle_data": {
        "cycle_length": 28,        // Days
        "last_period_date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
        "health_goals": ["goal1", "goal2"],
        "concerns": ["concern1"]
    },
    "updated_at": ISODate()
}
```

#### `messages` Collection
```javascript
{
    "user_id": "string",
    "role": "user" | "assistant",
    "content": "string",
    "ts": ISODate()
}
```

#### `summaries` Collection
```javascript
{
    "user_id": "string",
    "summary": "string",           // AI-generated session summary
    "ts": ISODate()
}
```

### In-Memory Fallback
When MongoDB is unavailable, data is stored in Python dictionaries:
- `_in_memory_users`: Dict[user_id, user_doc]
- `_in_memory_messages`: List[message_doc]
- `_in_memory_summaries`: List[summary_doc]

