## API Examples (cURL)

### Complete Workflow Example

```bash
# 1. Onboard a new user
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/onboarding \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "user_id": "jane_doe",
    "cycle_length": 28,
    "last_period_date": "2025-03-20",
    "health_goals": ["track mood", "reduce cramps", "better sleep"],
    "concerns": ["irregular cycles", "PMS"]
  }'

# 2. Chat with Shakti
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/chat \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "user_id": "jane_doe",
    "message": "What foods help with cramps?",
    "use_rag": true
  }'

# 3. Daily check-in
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/daily-checkin \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "user_id": "jane_doe",
    "mood": "tired",
    "pain_level": 6,
    "symptoms": ["cramps", "bloating", "headache"]
  }'

# 4. Learn about a topic
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/learn \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "user_id": "jane_doe",
    "topic": "luteal phase"
  }'

# 5. Get pattern insights
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/pattern-insight \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"user_id": "jane_doe"}'

# 6. Summarize session
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/summarize-session \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"user_id": "jane_doe"}'

# 7. Trigger proactive alert (simulating wearable data)
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/alert \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "user_id": "jane_doe",
    "stress_level": "high",
    "context": "Elevated heart rate detected at 2 AM"
  }'
```

